https://codeforces.com/problemset/problem/1837/B  
Approach :
We are given a string consisting of < and > signs.
These signs only tell us whether the next value should be greater or smaller than the previous one.
The actual numbers of the array are not important.
Only the order (up or down) matters.
If the same sign (< or >) appears continuously,
we must keep increasing or decreasing the value at each step.
To do this, we need a new different value for every step.
So, the minimum number of different values depends on
the longest continuous sequence of the same sign in the string.
We scan the string and find the maximum number of consecutive < or > characters.
If this maximum length is k, then the minimum cost will be k + 1.
We repeat this process for each test case and print the result.

